  <content_rating type="oars-1.1" />
  
  <description>
    <p>
      The Clipboard Project is your new second brain.

      This is an advanced clipboard manager that&apos;s super easy to use. Cut, copy and paste anything, anytime, anywhere with unlimited capacity, clipboards, and history! 

      Script CB to work superbly with your other favorite terminal tools. Integrate it with your existing system clipboards. Save time and effort the easy way.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can use CB from the desktop to monitor your clipboard status in real time.
      
      To use CB from the terminal, do "flatpak run app.getclipboard.Clipboard". If you'd like to use the command "cb" instead, do "alias cb='flatpak run app.getclipboard.Clipboard'" to make a shortcut. Then, add that to your terminal startup file like .bashrc so that it works every time.
    </p>
  </description>

